  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed Senate amended",
    "asOf": "2012-12-13",
    "date": "2013-01-04T16:50:55Z",
    "text": "Requires that the principal office of the U.S. Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims (CAVC) be in the metropolitan area of Washington, DC, but allows the CAVC to sit any place within the United States.\n\nRequires judges in active service on the CAVC to: (1) have their official duty station at the principal office; and (2) reside within 50 miles of such metropolitan area.\n\nAllows the President to remove judges violating that residency requirement who were confirmed on or after January 1, 2012.\n\nSets forth exceptions for recall-eligible retired judges."
  },
